📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `debi` command is used for managing Debian packages. You can use it to install, remove, or update packages on your system.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `debi install <package-name>` --> 📦 Install a new package.  Replace `<package-name>` with the actual package name.
    🔹 `debi remove <package-name>`  --> 🗑️ Remove a package from the system.
    🔹 `debi update`            --> 🔄 Get the latest package information from the repositories.
    🔹 `debi search <keyword>`    --> 🔍 Search for Debian packages based on a keyword.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ debi install firefox

    🔹 Installs the Firefox browser.

    $ debi remove libreoffice

    🔹 Removes the LibreOffice suite.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ debi update

    🔹 This command fetches the latest package lists from the repositories and prepares the system for updates.

